The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
Archives
 The City Diary
																																																		Bowbazar police on Monday detained a youth who was playing cricket near the intersection of Chittaranjan Avenue and Prinsep Street around 4.30pm. According to the police, the youth and his friends had illegally obstructed the intersection. Their cricket kit was seized. The youths friends ran away when the police reached the spot. He was later released.																																																		A jeweller in Titagarh, on the citys northern fringes, was arrested by officials of Bidhannagar (East) police station on Monday on charges of receiving stolen goods. Nine snatchers had been arrested from the area recently in a police swoop. During interrogation, they named the jeweller as the person to whom they sold the stolen articles. The accused would melt the ornaments and mould new ones, which he sold to his customers. 
